rComments: The class is pretty difficult. The midterm and final was tough- mostly applications. The labs are a lot of work but honestly the context of the course and lab was very interesting in my opinion. Lucas was patient, understanding and extremely available outside of class hours for anyone who needed it!

If there is something you dont understand take the time to go to his office hours. He will give a good explanation and will help you understand the concept! If you put the effort it you will do fine in this class

This class is a lot of work due to the weekly lab reports that are easy but so TIME CONSUMING . The prof is ok. He is very strict and stuck in his ways. He believes he can eliminate cheating so makes the exams 10x harder for the average non cheating student. The class material is interesting but this prof made this class harder then it had to be.

This was Michaud's first time teaching a class. He wasn't the most interesting prof, but he tried his best and put a lot of effort into the class. There were 10 lab reports, a midterm, and a final. Though you had to put a lot of work into the labs, it was easy to get a good grade on them. I also found the final a lot easier than the midterm.

Hes just not ready to teach. Lectures were filled with examples directly taken from studies, however his explanations really lacked. Leaves students to do most of their learning on their own. He mentions complex concepts without even defining them in the slides. Not for me.
